The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 27 October is 5,259 (608.7 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 22 October, there were 608 new confirmed cases (70.4 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 15 October, there were 399 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 52% ( 209 extra cases).
